The paper presents a variation of the Autoencoder that maximizes mutual information between input data and hidden representation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also compares the proposed model with state-of-the-art models in image processing (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses information theory to analyze the performance of the proposed model (cs.IT).
